      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "In section 1.1, our team identified that the training set values needs cleaning. In other words, by examining the summary statistics we can see that we having missing values as some features counts are less than the total number of table entries (e.g., our data set has 326 entries but hours_studied has a count value of 310), we have entries that violate the upper and lower bounds (e.g., the feature exam_score has a minimum of -20 and a maximum of 150 when the acceptable range of exam scores is 0-100). When examining the boxplot exam score we can spot 3 outliers. Missing values causes our data set to be incomplete and inaccurate, which can lead to our model dealing with more noise and increased errors. Duplicate entries and outliers introduces more noise to our model.\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "rYVP3qQ7JM3y"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "##1.2 Data Cleaning"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ou1i6dFlrowH"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "#1.2 Data Cleaning\n",
        "def clean_data(train_data, training=True):\n",
        "    train_data_clean = train_data.copy()\n",
        "\n",
        "    #Change the null values with the median of the dataset\n",
        "    for col in ['hours_studied', 'sleep_hours', 'attendance_rate', 'prev_exam_score']:\n",
        "        train_data_clean[col] = train_data_clean[col].fillna(train_data_clean[col].median())\n",
        "\n",
        "    #Cleaning the data: Hours Studied cannot be negative\n",
        "    train_data_clean['hours_studied'] = train_data_clean['hours_studied'].abs()\n",
        "\n",
        "    #Cleaning the data: Cannot sleep more than 24 hours\n",
        "    train_data_clean.loc[train_data_clean['sleep_hours'] > 24, 'sleep_hours'] = train_data_clean['sleep_hours'].median()\n",
        "    #Cleaning the data: If exam_score is higher than 50, pass\n",
        "    train_data_clean.loc[train_data_clean['exam_score'] >=50, 'passed'] = 1\n",
        "    train_data_clean.loc[train_data_clean['exam_score'] < 50, 'passed'] = 0\n",
        "\n",
        "    #Cap exam score between 100 and 0\n",
        "    train_data_clean.loc[train_data_clean['exam_score'] > 100, 'exam_score'] = 100\n",
        "    train_data_clean.loc[train_data_clean['exam_score'] <= 0, 'exam_score'] = 0\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Cap attendance at 100\n",
        "    train_data_clean.loc[train_data_clean['attendance_rate'] > 100, 'attendance_rate'] = 100\n",
        "    train_data_clean.loc[train_data_clean['attendance_rate'] <= 0, 'attendance_rate'] = 0\n",
        "\n",
        "    if training:\n",
        "        # Drop rows where exam scores are ridiculous\n",
        "        train_data_clean = train_data_clean[(train_data_clean['exam_score'] >= 0) & (train_data_clean['exam_score'] <= 100)]\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Drop duplicates\n",
        "        train_data_clean = train_data_clean.drop_duplicates()\n",
        "\n",
        "    return train_data_clean\n",
        "\n",
        "train_clean = clean_data(train_data, training=True)\n",
        "test_clean = clean_data(test_data, training=False)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"\\t\\tBefore Data Cleaning\")\n",
        "print(train_data.describe())\n",
        "print('\\n')\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"\\t\\tAfter Data Cleaning\")\n",
        "print(train_clean.describe())\n",
        "print('\\n')\n",
        "\n",
        "print(train_data.info())\n",
        "print('\\n')\n",
        "\n",
        "print(train_clean.info())\n",
        "print('\\n')\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"Original shape: {train_data.shape}, Cleaned shape: {train_clean.shape}\")\n",
        "print('\\n')\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(15, 5))\n",
        "plt.hist(train_clean['exam_score'].dropna(), bins=20)\n",
        "plt.xlabel('Exam Score')\n",
        "plt.ylabel('Frequency')\n",
        "plt.title('Exam Score Distribution')"
      ],
