      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "In section 1.3, we decided to exclude student_id, lucky_number, and sleep_hours. The feature student_id was excluded because this number is assigned to a student at random and cannot reasonably have an effect on exam performance as well as its low correlation score on the heatmap of 0.029. The feature lucky_number was excluded due to its low heatmap correlation score of -0.017. The feature attendance_rate was excluded due to its low heatmap correlation score of 0.27. The features prev_exam_score and hours_studied were included due to their heatmap correlation scores of 0.75 and 0.74 respectfully."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "G4LK87X5J8RS"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "##1.4 Data Normalization"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "f7czUYSlr0xO"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "#1.4 Data Normalization\n",
        "# Training Data\n",
        "X_train_simple = train_clean[simple_feat].values\n",
        "X_train_multi = train_clean[multi_feats].values\n",
        "y_train_regress = train_clean['exam_score'].values.reshape(-1, 1)\n",
        "y_train_class = train_clean['passed'].values.reshape(-1, 1)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Test Data\n",
        "X_test_simple = test_clean[simple_feat].values\n",
        "X_test_multi = test_clean[multi_feats].values\n",
        "y_test_regress = test_clean['exam_score'].values.reshape(-1, 1)\n",
        "y_test_class = test_clean['passed'].values.reshape(-1, 1)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Normalize (Z-Score) - Fit on Train, Apply to Test\n",
        "mean_s = np.mean(X_train_simple, axis=0)\n",
        "std_s = np.std(X_train_simple, axis=0)\n",
        "X_train_simple_norm = (X_train_simple - mean_s) / std_s\n",
        "X_test_simple_norm = (X_test_simple - mean_s) / std_s\n",
        "\n",
        "mean_m = np.mean(X_train_multi, axis=0)\n",
        "std_m = np.std(X_train_multi, axis=0)\n",
        "X_train_multi_norm = (X_train_multi - mean_m) / std_m\n",
        "X_test_multi_norm = (X_test_multi - mean_m) / std_m\n",
        "\n",
        "# L2 Normalization for 'hours_studied' (simple feature)\n",
        "l2_norm_hours_studied = np.linalg.norm(X_train_simple)\n",
        "X_train_simple_L2 = X_train_simple / l2_norm_hours_studied\n",
        "X_test_simple_L2 = X_test_simple / l2_norm_hours_studied"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "HXyIZ_YRozbM"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "By using normalization, we prevent domination from other features. In other words, by applying normalization we scale the features to similar range which also helps with gradient convergence."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ir3h1amtKcQ9"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "#2. Linear Regression\n",
        "##2.1 NumPy Implementation"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "tmdkMQbwr4OB"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "#2.1 Linear Regression\n",
        "#Using a single feature\n",
        "class SimpleLinearRegressionNumPy:\n",
        "    def __init__(self, learning_rate=0.01, iterations=1000):\n",
        "        self.lr = learning_rate\n",
        "        self.iterations = iterations\n",
        "        self.beta1 = None\n",
        "        self.beta0 = None\n",
        "        self.loss_history = []\n",
        "\n",
        "    def mse_loss(self, y_true, y_pred):\n",
        "        return np.mean((y_true - y_pred) ** 2)\n",
        "\n",
        "    def fit(self, X, y):\n",
        "        n_samples = X.shape[0]\n",
        "        self.beta1 = 0.0\n",
        "        self.beta0 = 0.0\n",
        "\n",
        "        for _ in range(self.iterations):\n",
        "            y_pred = np.dot(X,self.beta1) + self.beta0\n",
        "\n",
        "            # Gradient Calculation\n",
        "            d_beta1 = (2 / n_samples) * np.sum((y_pred - y)*X)\n",
        "            d_beta0 = (2 / n_samples) * np.sum(y_pred - y)\n",
        "\n",
        "            self.beta1 -= self.lr * d_beta1\n",
        "            self.beta0 -= self.lr * d_beta0\n",
        "            self.loss_history.append(self.mse_loss(y, y_pred))\n",
        "\n",
        "    def predict(self, X):\n",
        "        return np.dot(X,self.beta1) + self.beta0\n",
        "\n",
        "# Train One Feature Linear Regression\n",
        "lin_reg = SimpleLinearRegressionNumPy(learning_rate=0.01, iterations=2000)\n",
        "lin_reg.fit(X_train_simple_norm, y_train_regress)\n",
